        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 6 at 9:54AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Patchy fog dense fog continues over portions of the Helena Valley
and along sections of highway 287 bordering Canyon Ferry Lake,
especially on the north side of the lake. This will continue for
the next couple of hours before dissipating early this afternoon.

Those traveling in the Helena Valley and along highway 287 in
between Three Forks and Helena should be prepared for highly
variable conditions across short distances with visibility falling
as low as a quarter mile or less. Slow down and allow extra time
to reach your destination.
</description>
